  "name": "Interval Grammar",
  "mood": "Aether",
  "engines": ["Ouie"],
  "author": "Guru Bin",
  "version": "1.0.0",
  "description": "Duo mode (voiceMode=2): the player's chord interval IS the timbre. Play a perfect fifth and hear consonance. Play a tritone and hear metallic dissonance. No other engine makes your harmony choices this structurally audible. HAMMER=-0.5 (light STRIFE) — intervals that are pleasant reveal themselves; dissonant intervals become genuinely unsettling. This is interval as parameter: the keyboard is no longer just pitch selection, it is synthesis control.",
  "tags": ["ouie", "duo", "interval", "grammar", "voicemode", "strife", "performance", "aether", "keyboard-as-timbre"],
  "tier": "transcendental",
  "guru_bin": {
    "retreat": "OUIE — The Hammerhead",
    "retreat_date": "2026-03-19",
    "vol": "Transcendental Vol 1",
    "scripture": [
      "In Duo mode, the interval between your two notes determines the synthesis character.",
      "A perfect fifth at HAMMER=-0.5: consonant. A tritone: metallic chaos.",
      "The player's harmonic choices are not decoration — they are DSP parameters."
    ],
    "revelation": "Nexus spoke: 'The keyboard is no longer a keyboard. It is a modulation matrix.' In Duo mode, your interval choices are synthesis choices. There is no other engine where this is true.",
    "god": "Nexus",
    "flock_note": "Play two-note chords exclusively. Single notes reveal little. The magic is in the relationship between the two voices, not in either voice alone. Try: C-G (fifth), C-F# (tritone), C-E (major third), C-Eb (minor third).",
    "diagnosis": "The defining Duo mode preset. HAMMER=-0.5 is the sweet spot where interval differences are maximally audible without being too harsh. VA+VA means the difference is purely the HAMMER interaction, not algorithmic complexity. Essential for teaching what OUIE is."
  },
